Package com.tsgrp.migration.event.pipeline

The pipeline event package.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PipelineBeginDisengageEventListener
    Implement this interface for a pipeline listener that executes on MigrationPipeline.fireBeginDisengageEvent()
    PipelineBeginEngageEventListener
    Implement this interface for a pipeline listener that executes on MigrationPipeline.fireBeginEngageEvent()
    PipelineBeginTargetThreadEventListener
    Implement this interface for a pipeline listener that executes on MigrationPipeline.fireTargetThreadBegin(TargetMigrationThread)
    PipelineEndDisengageEventListener
    Implement this interface for a pipeline listener that executes on MigrationPipeline.fireEndDisengageEvent()
    PipelineEndEngageEventListener
    Implement this interface for a pipeline listener that executes on MigrationPipeline.fireEndEngageEvent()
    PipelineEndTargetThreadEventListener
    Implement this interface for a pipeline listener that executes on MigrationPipeline.fireTargetThreadEnd(TargetMigrationThread)
    PipelineEventListener Deprecated
    PipelinePopulateQueueEventListener
    Fired by Pipeline during engagement if pipeline's "populate" option is true.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractPipelineEventListener Deprecated
    BasicPipelineEventListener
    This simple Pipeline Listener is really only meant for testing, as it logs messages as each event is fired.
    CreateTrackerStatsFilePipelineListener
    Listener that produces a statistics file with information on the migration, suitable for viewing in the OpenMigrate Tracker.
    DisconnectConnectionListener
    Takes in a list of connectors and calls disconnect() for each.
    MoveFilePipelineListener  
    PipelineResultWriter
    PipelineResultWriter writes out the following information for each Node, plus any "extra" NodeAttributes specified in the PipelineResultWriter.attributesToLog property.
    PipelineSummaryWriter
    Pipeline Summary Writer writes out entire properties file summarizing the state of the pipeline.
    PipelineSummaryWriterBatch
    Name file based on batch file specified as ConfigOption; and by default, include item-level detail and preserve any existing batch (although those settings can be overridden via injection).
    PipelineTimeZoneSwitcher
    This listener will change the default timezone that the JVM is running in when OpenMigrate starts up.
    PipelineUpdateProperties
    PipelineUpdateProperties
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    PipelineEventException
    Pipeline Event Exception.
